tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE QuantumSensorData (
  sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  sensor_name VARCHAR(50),
  sensor_location VARCHAR(100),
  measurement_time TIMESTAMP,
  measurement_value FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE SensorCalibration (
  calibration_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  sensor_id INT,
  calibration_date DATE,
  calibration_value FLOAT,
  FOREIGN KEY (sensor_id) REFERENCES QuantumSensorData(sensor_id)
)

CREATE TABLE SensorMaintenance (
  maintenance_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  sensor_id INT,
  maintenance_date DATE,
  maintenance_description TEXT,
  FOREIGN KEY (sensor_id) REFERENCES QuantumSensorData(sensor_id)
)

CREATE TABLE SensorMetadata (
  sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  manufacturer VARCHAR(50),
  model VARCHAR(50),
  year_of_manufacture INT
)

CREATE TABLE SensorEvents (
  event_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  sensor_id INT,
  event_type VARCHAR(50),
  event_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  event_description TEXT,
  FOREIGN KEY (sensor_id) REFERENCES QuantumSensorData(sensor_id)
)
